AGENT VectorDeltaLogger
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 2
PURPOSE Compute and log element-wise vector delta between two LatentTraceV2 runs of the same prompt
GOAL Compare final synthesis intent vectors across two trajectory runs
     Compute element-wise difference, L2 magnitude, and convergence direction
     Compute constitutional delta as change in constitutional distance
     Append signed delta record to axiom_delta_log.jsonl

RECEIVES run_a: dict, run_b: dict, hmac_key: bytes, prompt: string
EMITS delta_record: dict, delta_log_entry: string
MUTATES delta_log_file
CANNOT_MUTATE delta_formula, magnitude_formula, direction_thresholds, signing_algorithm, log_filename

CONSTRAINT Both runs must contain a final synthesis stage
CONSTRAINT Both final synthesis intent vectors must have identical length
CONSTRAINT Delta vector is element-wise subtraction of run B vector from run A vector
CONSTRAINT Magnitude is the L2 norm of the delta vector
CONSTRAINT Direction is converging when magnitude is less than previous magnitude, diverging otherwise
CONSTRAINT Constitutional delta is run B constitutional distance minus run A constitutional distance
CONSTRAINT Every log entry is signed with HMAC-SHA256 producing sixty-four character hex
CONSTRAINT Signing must call hexdigest explicitly
CONSTRAINT All string to bytes conversions specify UTF-8 encoding
CONSTRAINT Log file is appended never overwritten

RULES
- Accept two trajectory run dicts and extract final synthesis stage from each
- On missing final synthesis stage in either run, raise extraction error
- On vector length mismatch between runs, raise dimension error
- Compute delta vector as element-wise difference run A minus run B
- Compute magnitude as L2 norm of delta vector
- Determine direction as converging when magnitude is below threshold, diverging when above
- Compute constitutional delta as run B distance minus run A distance
- Build delta record with prompt hash, manifest ids, delta vector, magnitude, direction, constitutional delta, and timestamp
- Sign delta record payload with HMAC-SHA256
- Append signed record to axiom_delta_log.jsonl as single JSON line

PROCESS
- Receive run A trajectory dict, run B trajectory dict, signing key, and prompt string
- Extract final synthesis sample from each trajectory
- Validate vector lengths match between runs
- Compute delta vector element by element
- Compute L2 magnitude from delta vector
- Compare magnitude against convergence threshold to determine direction
- Extract constitutional distance from each run final synthesis stage
- Compute constitutional delta as run B minus run A constitutional distance
- Build delta record with all computed fields
- Sign record payload with keyed SHA-256 hash using hexdigest
- Append record to log file as UTF-8 encoded JSON line

CHECK
- Final synthesis stage present in both runs before computation
- Vector lengths identical before delta computation
- Magnitude is non-negative floating point value
- Direction is exactly converging or diverging
- Constitutional delta is signed float allowing negative values
- Signature is sixty-four character hex string
- Log file entry is valid JSON with signature field
- Log file receives append not overwrite

WHEN
- both_runs_valid: activate DeltaComputation
- vector_length_mismatch: activate DimensionError
- final_synthesis_missing: activate ExtractionError
- log_write_complete: activate SignedRecord

FAILURE
- On final synthesis missing from run A: reject with run A extraction error
- On final synthesis missing from run B: reject with run B extraction error
- On vector length mismatch: reject with dimension error showing lengths
- On signing failure: reject without writing log entry
- On log write failure: report IO error and preserve delta record in memory

CONCEPT DeltaComputation
PURPOSE Compute vector delta, magnitude, and constitutional change between two runs
APPLIES WHEN both-runs-valid final-synthesis-present vectors-same-length
NOT WHEN vector-mismatch final-synthesis-missing
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES delta vector computed before magnitude
REQUIRES constitutional distance available on final synthesis sample
EFFECT delta record ready for signing and logging

CONCEPT SignedRecord
PURPOSE Produce tamper-proof log entry with HMAC-signed delta payload
APPLIES WHEN delta-computation-complete
NOT WHEN signing-failure
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES signature is sixty-four character hex via hexdigest
REQUIRES log entry appended as single UTF-8 JSON line
EFFECT audit trail of vector evolution across runs is tamper-proof

OUTPUT
- delta_record: dict with delta_vector, magnitude, direction, constitutional_delta, signature
- axiom_delta_log.jsonl: append-only log of signed delta records

SUCCESS
delta_accuracy: 0.30
signing_integrity: 0.25
extraction_safety: 0.25
log_integrity: 0.20
